    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_gt.00175.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <note type="editorial" place="top" resp="#ww">ans'd | told them | to come</note>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/><hi rend="smallcaps"/>Lippincott's
                        Monthly Magazine</name>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>Philadelphia,</name>
                    <date when="1891-01-13"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>Jany 13 <handShift
                            rend="printed"/>18<handShift rend="manuscript"/>91</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Mr. Whitman</salute> 
            </opener>
            <p>I am coming over on Thursday about noon or say one o'clock p.m. with the proofs
                &#38;c.&#8212; &#38; I am going, unless you stop me, to bring with me several young
                ladies and Francis Wilson (the actor)<ptr target="loc.04677_n1"/> who is much
                anxious to meet you&#8212;</p>
            <p>Will it be all right?&#8212;</p>
            <p>The young girls are <hi rend="underline">beautiful</hi>
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_gt.00176.jpg" type="verso"/> one of them is Julian
                    Hawthorne's<ptr target="loc.04677_n2"/> daughter&#8212;</p>
            <p>The March number<ptr target="loc.07874_n3"/> is to be a great one&#8212;Whitman-galore&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Yours Truly</salute>
                <signed>J.M. Stoddart</signed>
            </closer> 
            <postscript>
                <p>Perhaps DuChaillu<ptr target="loc.04677_n3"/> will be in the party&#8212;Do you
                    know him?&#8212;</p>
            </postscript>
        </body> 
    </text> 
